title: Bunny Brown and his Sister Sue at Christmas Tree Cove
creator: Laura Lee Hope
description: LibriVox recording of Bunny Brown and his Sister Sue at Christmas Tree Cove, by Laura Lee Hope. Read as a duet by Rose264 and Sean McGaughey. Bunny Brown and His Sister Sue were featured in a series of 20 books for young children published by the Stratemeyer Syndicate from 1916-1930. In this adventure, first published in 1920, Bunny and Sue lose a valuable possession belonging to their mother. They have many adventures and misadventures during a family boating vacation to Christmas Tree Cove. (Introduction by S. McGaughey) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
